Jordon Ibe is poised to sign a new five-year contract with Liverpool by the end of the week.

The 19-year-old has agreed terms on a deal which will keep him at Anfield until 2020.

Ibe spent the first half of this season on loan at Derby County but returned to Liverpool in January and has made a notable impact in his eight appearances. 

