A knee injury disrupted his run in the side and he was cup-tied for Sunday’s FA Cup semi-final defeat to Aston Villa, but he is expected to return against West Brom this weekend.

Liverpool also expect to announce Jordan Henderson's new contract this week and are close to finalising an extension for Martin Skrtel.

Talks are ongoing with young defender Jon Flanagan too whose contract expires in June.

Liverpool yesterday agreed a new three-year shirt sponsorship deal with Standard Chartered worth around £30million a year.

